---
title: Herbed Chicken Sandwiches with Saucy Onion, Lemony Potato Wedges & Dijonnaise
description: You’ve got your Chicago deep dish pizza and your Chicago-style hot dog, but do you know about the iconic Chicago pork chop sandwich? Shh, it’s a little hometown secret, and this is a super tasty riff on that classic. In our version, seasoned and seared boneless chops and sliced onion (cooked in pan drippings!) fill toasty buns smeared with Dijonnaise. Crispy lemon-kissed potato wedges stand in for fries in this variation on a Chi-town sensation!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/herbed-pork-chop-sandwiches-79c5d67c.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65d64d3fdc1b8ee2a5df7ea1.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/herbed-chicken-sandwiches-65d64d3fdc1b8ee2a5df7ea1
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 940 kcal
  fat: 45 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 77 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1420 mg
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced) (whole onion for 4). Zest and quarter @lemon{1}(zested and quartered). Halve @potato buns{2}.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} (spread across entire sheet for 4 servings) with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}, half the @fry seasoning{1/2%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack for ~{12%minutes}. (You'll add more to the sheet then.)

While potatoes roast, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels. Season with half the @celery salt{1/2%teaspoon} (all for 4 servings), half the @dried thyme{1/2%teaspoon} (you'll use more later), @fry seasoning{1/2%tablespoon} (remaining), and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in pork for chicken. Cook until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes per side. (Skip roasting for pork.)

Once potatoes have roasted 12 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully place chicken on empty side of sheet; return to top rack and roast until chicken is cooked through and potatoes are browned and tender, ~{8-10%minutes} more. (For 4, leave potatoes roasting; add chicken to a second #baking sheet{} and roast on middle rack.)

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add sliced onion; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in a drizzle of oil, @flour{1%tablespoon}, and remaining thyme. Cook, stirring, until mixture is lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Whisk in @water{1/2%cup} (1 cup for 4), @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and @sugar{1/4%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4). Bring to a simmer; cook, whisking constantly, until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; season with salt and pepper to taste.

> Use pan used for chicken here.

While onion cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, and juice from one lemon wedge (juice from two wedges for 4 servings).

Toast buns directly on top rack of oven until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Toss potatoes with lemon zest.

Spread a thin layer of creamy mustard sauce onto cut sides of buns. Fill buns with chicken and saucy onion.

Divide sandwiches and potatoes between plates. Serve with remaining lemon wedges and remaining creamy mustard sauce on the side for dipping.